nment function, Spigel highlights how TV snapshots complicate understandings of the significance of television in everyday life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPhotographyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPopular culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aTelevision viewerszUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aTelevisionxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022893?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022893/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles